  "text": "The cardiac architecture of the healthy heart is Gothic (elliptical), while that of the sick heart is Romanesque (spherical) [CITATION_1] . Ingels [CITATION_2] emphasized the importance of the 'opposing force couples' from subendocardial fibres disposed in a right handed helix and subepicardial fibres in a left handed helix. The summation of these force couples generates the torsional deformation of the left ventricle about its long axis.",
